  "prompt": "When is the best marriage age for a girl?",
  "response": "There's no universally \"best\" marriage age, as it depends on individual circumstances, personal readiness, cultural background, and personal goals. However, many experts suggest some general considerations:\n\n1. Emotional maturity\n- Late 20s to early 30s\n- Better understanding of self and relationships\n- More stable emotional state\n\n2. Financial stability\n- Established career\n- Financial independence\n- Ability to support a household\n\n3. Personal development\n- Completed education\n- Explored personal interests\n- Developed strong sense of identity\n\n4. Biological factors\n- Reproductive health considerations\n- Physical and mental readiness\n\n5. Psychological research suggests\n- Between 28-32 years old can be favorable\n- Lower divorce rates for marriages at this age range\n\nUltimately, successful marriages depend more on:\n- Mutual understanding\n- Compatibility\n- Communication skills\n- Shared values\n- Emotional intelligence\n\nEach person's journey is unique, and there's no one-size-fits-all approach to marriage. Personal readiness and individual circumstances matter most.",
